      "writtenOn": "2019-10-10T18:55:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, I\u0027m not sure... I had interpreted it more as \"some entity requested by the client\", whereas in this case we\u0027re sort of /deciding/ we need the isolated outputs and so fetching them from isolated.\n\nI chose \"FailedPrecondition\" because it seems like if this failed, the client should know that it\u0027s something weird with the underlying system (expected outputs missing), rather than that the client asked for something that doesn\u0027t exist (because since we got here, it /should/ exist).\n\nWhat do you think of that? I\u0027m fine with switching it to NotFound too, I agree it\u0027s fuzzy.",
